==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eucalyn
<hw>Eu"ca*lyn</hw> <pr>(⟦umac⟧"k⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An unfermentable sugar, obtained as an
uncrystallizable sirup by the decomposition of melitose; also obtained
from a Tasmanian <gen>eucalyptus</gen>, -- whence its name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>eucalypt</ent>⟦br⟧
